text:
Rishabh Kaushikk
@RishabhKaushikk
Follow
Ladke hai hum, naam to humaara hi aata
hai na
Koi jaanwar kisi ki beti k sath khele,
ilzaam to hum par hi aata hai na.
Ki ek dum se generalize kar dia jaata hai,
all men are dog,
Pr wafadaari mein to us bezubaan se
achha kon hi hai
Najaane kyu pr duniya is bhedbhav pr
maun si hai
Han har ladka to galat nahi hota, na har
ladki sahi hoti hai
Par samaaj mein najaane kitni hi buri
baate kahi gayi hai.
Zara unse to pucho, jo hume qareeb se
jaante hai.
Hum to apne dosto ki bhen ko b apni hi
bhen maante hai.
Najaane kitne hi rishte hum bakhoobi
nibaate hai,
Par ek galat ghatna, or hum sab hi ek
jaise ho jaate hai.
translated_text:
We are boys, our name is always there
isn't it
If some animal plays with someone's daughter,
the blame always comes on us.
That it is generalized completely,
all men are dog,
But in loyalty, who is better than that speechless one
Don't know why the world remains silent on this discrimination
No, not every boy is wrong, nor is every
girl right
But in society, who knows how many bad
things have been said.
Ask them, who know us closely.
We consider our friends' sisters as our own
sisters.
We fulfill so many relationships beautifully,
But due to one wrong incident, we all become
the same.
